         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <choice corresp="#a1">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>691</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// he will carry (it) away, without sin. 8</seg></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Der Eigentümer [wtl. wem es zu eigen ist, der] wird es [ab]holen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The owner [lit. who[ever] it belongs to, he] will come for it.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>363</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:broomhead1962"/><citedRange>90</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a2">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// with (three) proper (materials) the proper (colour) should be done.</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a3">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// or ... If he does not do (the proper colour), Pāt. 9 If a monk</seg></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">if he does not do it—pātayantika. [5]9</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>691</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// except for the occasion, Pāt. There is the following occasion. ... of the heat</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b1">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// of ... These are the occasions here. 60 || If a monk</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b2">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>47</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// (1) If a monk evokes the doubt of a monk, Pāt.</seg></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">(Wenn) ein Mönch [wtl. welcher Mönch] einem Mönch Zweifel verursacht, [so ist das] ein Pātayantika[-Vergehen].</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">(If) a monk [lit. whichever monk] causes doubt in a[nother] monk, [this is] a pātayantika [offence].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>330</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b3">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// (2) If a monk tickles a monk, Pāt. 3 If a monk in the water</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b4">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>218</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// (4 If a monk) lies in one cover (with a woman), Pāt. 5 If a monk (frightens a monk or orders to frighten)</seg></seg>
               </choice>
            </p>
         </div>
